Re: 「臭い所が捨てられない」って、どういう意味？
by Ongakuka » Tue 02.28.2012 10:43 am 臭い 所 が 捨てられない = can't get rid of the fact that (he/she/it) is smelly. 'tokoro' means 'feature' hereIt is the speaker who is saying they will apologizeSince the title of your thread is a request, please use more formal Japanese (i.e 「臭い所が捨てられない」とはどういう意味ですかI hope that helps
なぜなら、おまえは・・・・・・人形だ
Ongakuka
