Re: 「臭い所が捨てられない」って、どういう意味？
by SomeCallMeChris » Tue 02.28.2012 1:13 pm Ongakuka wrote:臭い 所 が 捨てられない = can't get rid of the fact that (he/she/it) is smelly. 'tokoro' means 'feature' hereOh, potential not passive... of course. That makes more sense, my bad.It is the speaker who is saying they will apologizeI don't see how you can know this, although it seems like a likely interpretation of the line in isolation... but... A says "Smelly's all right. Can't help being smelly."B says "You mean that monkey?"A says "Ahh, that's no good, if I'm someone says that to me then I'll apologize."Hnhhh... ? In the tiny context we have, I have trouble seeing it being 'when someone says that to me I will apologize'.
